headline: Cummins India's quarterly profit rises on higher engine, generator demand
summary: The company, a unit of U.S.-based truck engine maker Cummins Inc, said its consolidated profit after tax rose to 6.04 billion rupees ($69.05 million) from 4.63 billion rupees a year ago.  Demand for power generation equipment typically rises in the summer due to increased electricity consumption from cooling systems and a higher risk of grid overloads or outages, which helps companies like Cummins India.
